[/code]

The program takes a simple text format model and converts it to a dat file.
example...

[code]
Material 2
54397
0
vertex 8
-160 68 25
-154 68 25
-146 70 25
-140 75 25
-136 82 25
-136 87 25
-137 92 25
-143 99 25
face 4
0 1 2 1
1 2 3 1
4 5 6 0
5 6 7 0
Eof
[/code]

Faces are triangles, the 4th number is the material used.

The model was generated in metasequoia, a simple search and replace is needed to remove all the garbage, to get to the simple text file.

NOTE: this does not 'compress' the file, it just converts it.
ALSO: You can obtain materials from an existing .dat exported to .mqo :)

One day i'll get around to making it useful and idiot proof, until then have fun!!!!



P.S. Does anyone need me to explain how you get compressed files?

